syncfix-fix13: Accept protocol version 0 from old nodes (ROOT CAUSE FIX)

Old nodes (6f and stock) never set the version field in message headers,
leaving it at 0 (zero-initialized). The new code only accepted versions
8 (LEGACY) and 9 (CURRENT), silently dropping ALL messages from old
validators. This prevented collecting enough signs/precommits to
complete any block.

Fix: Add version 0 to s_protocol_version_is_supported().

This was Bug #4 - the root cause of 7+ hours of no signing on the new build.

Applied to:
- dap_chain_cs_esbocs.c: s_protocol_version_is_supported function
